  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Cerebral toxoplasmosis in HIV-positive or AIDS patients, usually seen as ring-enhancing lesions on CT or MRI",
        "Toxoplasmosis can also present as disseminated infection, though much less common.",
        "Most individuals (>95%) will have IgG evidence of preexisting latent infection, but acute new infection also reported.",
        "Antibody titers often very low, borderline positive.",
        "Regimens for:",
        "Treatment",
        "Primary prophylaxis in AIDS patients who are IgG toxoplasma antibody positive and who have CD4 count <100/mL",
        "Chronic suppression after treatment",
        "See guidelines: clinicalinfo.HIV.gov"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Toxoplasma gondii"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Treatment:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Treat for minimum of 6 weeks after resolution of signs/symptoms, followed by suppressive therapy (see below)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "regimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Pyrimethamine",
                "dose": "200 mg x 1 po, then (75 mg po daily for those weighing \u226560 kg) or (50 mg po daily for those weighing <60 kg)"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Sulfadiazine",
                "dose": "(1.5 gm if \u226560 kg or 1 gm if <60 kg)",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "q6h",
                "connector": "+"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Folinic acid",
                "dose": "10-25 mg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "daily",
                "connector": "+"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Primary Prophylaxis:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Can discontinue if CD4 count >200 for 3 months"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "regimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "prophylaxis",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "TMP-SMX-DS",
                "dose": "1 tab",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "q24h"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Chronic Suppression (secondary prophylaxis):"
        },
        {
          "type": "regimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "suppression",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Sulfadiazine",
                "dose": "2-4 gm",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "divided in 2-4 doses/day"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Pyrimethamine",
                "dose": "25-50 mg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "q24h",
                "connector": "+"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Folinic acid",
                "dose": "10-25 mg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "q24h",
                "connector": "+"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "regimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "suppression",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "TMP-SMX-DS",
                "dose": "1 tab",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "BID (preferred) or q24h"
              }
            ],
            "notes": "--less clinical experience but may be used to reduce pills or if pyrimethamine not available."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Can discontinue suppression if CD4 count >200 for 6 months"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
